    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-12-30T15:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-12-30T15:48:00-05:00" n="490"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751J.00/12–3053: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Legation at Vientiane</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d490fn1">Drafted by <persName>Getz</persName> of <gloss
                            target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>. Repeated for information to Saigon as 1134
                        and Paris as 2340.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-12-30T15:48:00-05:00"
                            >December 30, 1953—3:48 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Secretary yesterday received Lao Minister and handed reply latter’s note
                    December 26 which transmitted text <persName corresp="#p_SP2">Souvanna
                        Phouma</persName> declaration.<note n="2" xml:id="d490fn2">Neither the
                        Laotian note nor a record of the conversation between the Secretary of State
                        and the Laotian Ambassador on Dec. 29 has been found in Department of State
                        files. A briefing memorandum by <persName corresp="#p_DEF1"
                            >Drumright</persName> to the Secretary regarding the conversation, Dec.
                        29, is in file 751J.00/12–2953.</note> Text reply follows (complimentary
                    opening omitted): <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Secretary of State would be most grateful if Minister would convey to
                            Prime Minister expression his appreciation of clarity, conciseness and
                            logic of declaration. U.S. fully aware of aims Communist imperialism as
                            represented by Viet Minh, whose false claim to be allied with
                            nationalism Laos now again effectively unmasked.”</p>
                        <p>“Secretary of State takes opportunity reiterate determination U.S.
                            Government continue its material assistance to armed forces French <pb
                                facs="0968" n="936" xml:id="pg_936"/> Union including those Laos in
                            their heroic fight against Communist aggression and imperialism.
                            Secretary of State desires also reiterate his admiration of brave
                            struggle being conducted by people of Laos under leadership Royal
                            Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Decided here public release this text more appropriately done by Lao Government
                    Vientiane. You therefore authorized tell Lao U.S. has no objection such action.
                    Lao Minister here informed and agrees. Notify Department when release made.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d490fn3">In telegram 18 from Vientiane, Jan. 2, 1954, it was
                        reported that the text had been published in Vientiane on Dec. 30.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
